[
  {
    "text": "Betsy Langowski: Linking against the 12.1 SDK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "will allow your app to take advantage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the full displays on the new iPad Pros.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=6"
  },
  {
    "text": "Not only does the 11-inch iPad Pro ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "feature a brand-new screen size and a new aspect ratio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "both devices now have rounded corners ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "and no Home button.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "You may need to do a little bit of work ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "to make sure your iPad apps look great on these devices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "but there are a lot of resources available.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=23"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if you've been following best practices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "that work should be very minimal.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you've adapted an iPhone app for iPhone X or later, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll find this process very familiar on iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "Adapting safe area insets throughout your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=36"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as making sure to not special case per device model, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the best way to future proof your application.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more technical information about how to do that, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=46"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as information about edge cases ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the times when you can't use these techniques, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "see the video \"Building apps for iPhone X\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Building apps for iPhone XS, iPhone XS Max, and iPhone XR.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here are two examples of the most common mistakes made ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "when running apps on the new iPad Pros.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=66"
  },
  {
    "text": "For much more specific design information, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out the related video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Designing for iPad Pro and Apple Pencil.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's a very simple iPad app that looks OK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=76"
  },
  {
    "text": "when built for an iPad with a Home button.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "But when I run it on a new 11-inch iPad Pro, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can see that the tab bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=84"
  },
  {
    "text": "interferes with the Home indicator.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "A common reason this happens, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the reason it's happening here, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "is because while this looks like a standard tab bar, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's actually a custom tab bar.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "Safe area insets given by Interface Builder ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "have been ignored and this custom content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=98"
  },
  {
    "text": "has instead been aligned with the edge of the view.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another reason this may happen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "is if you're not using storyboards ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "and are instead using API to identify the screen bounds.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "The absolute best way to fix this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "is to simply use storyboards and safe area insets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as native UI elements.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your app will look great across devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you'll be future proofed.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=118"
  },
  {
    "text": "Take a look at another app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a full-screen game with custom UI elements.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=122"
  },
  {
    "text": "It looks great on an iPad with a Home button, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "but on the new 11-inch iPad Pro, there are a few problems.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "The content at the top and bottom is cut off ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the custom buttons feel too close ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the new rounded corners.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "This can happen for a number of reasons.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this case, that app is assuming ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "a four-by-three aspect ratio, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is no longer true for all iPads.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you have a Metal app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "or are using API level adjustment, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll need to go back to your designer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "and make sure your designs are conforming to safe areas ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "and being mindful of the new rounded corners.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "In games in particular, it's also important to ensure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=157"
  },
  {
    "text": "you didn't have any controls or gestures related to game play ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "near the Home indicator as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=163"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you don't link against the 12.1 SDK, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=166"
  },
  {
    "text": "your app will be running compatibility mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "While running at the full screen size ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=171"
  },
  {
    "text": "is a much more immersive experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "linking against the 12.1 SDK is important for another reason.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPad, apps can run side by side, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "like Maps and Clock, seen here.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even if your app has been linked against 12.1, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "if people are running it side by side ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "with an app that hasn't been updated, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "both apps run in a new kind of compatibility mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=190"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's a simple test app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's been rebuilt with a 12.1 SDK, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=195"
  },
  {
    "text": "so now it takes advantage of the full display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=198"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the new 11-inch iPad Pro.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here it is running side by side with Maps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=203"
  },
  {
    "text": "another app that's linked against 12.1, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "and they both look great.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "Still taking advantage of the entire screen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "But when it's run side by side with the WWDC app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "which hasn't yet been linked against 12.1, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "the test app is now forced back ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "into a new kind of combability mode of common insets.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "By updating your app quickly, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "not only do you get the more immersive experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "you ensure that the other apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "that may be running side by side with your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "maintain their immersive experience.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "This common inset combability mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "doesn't reflect a real life configuration of hardware ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "and so your apps haven't necessarily been tested in it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is another great reason why using safe area insets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "and auto layout is a good idea.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's important to design your apps and write your code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "in such a way that they can run on whatever trait ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "or combination of traits they detect, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "regardless of hardware.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "By taking some time to ensure your iPad apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=259"
  },
  {
    "text": "can handle this common inset combability mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll also be ensuring a smooth transition next year ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=264"
  },
  {
    "text": "when you can bring UIKit apps to the Mac.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "This year we've introduced a brand-new Apple Pencil.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "All of the feature set from the original Apple Pencil remains, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "but we've introduced a new gesture ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "unique to the second-generation Apple Pencil: the double tap.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "Double tap enables three new actions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "all configurable in the Settings app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "People can switch between the current tool they're using ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the eraser.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "They can switch between the tool they're using ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the last tool they used, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "or they can show the color palette.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "People can also turn off double tap entirely.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app supports the Apple Pencil, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "but doesn't have a drawing or tooling element, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can implement custom actions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=306"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, these should be used very judiciously.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is what your implementation might look like.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can find more robust sample code in the related resources.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "In your app view, you detect the double tap event ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "by creating UIPencilInteraction object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "and assigning a delegate to it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also add customization, if appropriate for your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "Remember, your app will continue to be used and loved ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "by your customers on iPads ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=331"
  },
  {
    "text": "that pair with the original Apple Pencil.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "So it's important not to gate functionality ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "behind the double tap gesture.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your customized interactions should never be the default.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your app should always reflect the system settings ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then give people an option to change to a custom action.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reflecting the system gestures is as simple as calling ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIPencilInteraction. preferredTapAction ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "and handling the four built-in cases ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=356"
  },
  {
    "text": "as reflected in the Settings app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad Pro now has a high-speed USB-C port.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=361"
  },
  {
    "text": "This enables dynamic range and frame matching, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is familiar from Apple TV.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad Pro supports HDR 4K up to 60 Hz ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=369"
  },
  {
    "text": "and external displays of up to 5K.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=374"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's no special adaption necessary.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "Everything that already worked for you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your second screen support will continue to work.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "USB-C is a high-speed USB port, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=383"
  },
  {
    "text": "which enables many of the same pro-level technologies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you have brought to your Mac, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "including USB audio, USB Ethernet, and USB MIDI.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "And it also allows for simultaneous output.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "This facilitates, for example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=398"
  },
  {
    "text": "connecting a DSLR camera and a 5K display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your iPad Pro at the same time.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on how to build ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=405"
  },
  {
    "text": "fantastic second screen support into your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out the WWDC 2018 video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Adding Delight to Your iOS App.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=413"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad Pro brings Face ID to the iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "Unlike the iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "there is no TrueDepth camera housing.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "The camera sits in-line with the bezel.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=423"
  },
  {
    "text": "Face ID works in portrait, as well as in landscape.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app uses Touch ID for authentication, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll automatically get the new Face ID behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "and your existing code will be compatible.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=434"
  },
  {
    "text": "Just like when you adapted your app for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll need to do a couple of things ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "for proper robust Face ID support.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll need to add a localized NSFaceIDUsageDescription string ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=445"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your plist so your app properly asks for consent ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=449"
  },
  {
    "text": "to use Face ID.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "Make sure you update your strings to reflect Face ID.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can do this manually, or even better, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use the local authentication property, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "Biometry type, introduced in iOS 11, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "to handle this check for you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=464"
  },
  {
    "text": "Consider the order of your authentication flow.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "Since Face ID is an automatic action, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "avoid authenticating immediately upon launch.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=471"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let your customer choose ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=474"
  },
  {
    "text": "when they'd like to begin the authentication flow ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=476"
  },
  {
    "text": "so they're ready.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "For much more information, including sample code, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "see the related video \"Face ID and your Apps.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new 11-inch and 12.9-inch iPad Pros ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=487"
  },
  {
    "text": "are the most powerful iPads yet.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "Their packed with new technologies that will empower ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=492"
  },
  {
    "text": "exciting Core ML and machine learning apps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "enable Metal-based games ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "to deliver their most beautiful experience yet, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "and drive ARKit 2 and the next generation of AR apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=502"
  },
  {
    "text": "But one of the best features of iPad Pro ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=506"
  },
  {
    "text": "is how simple it will be for you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=509"
  },
  {
    "text": "to bring your existing applications to these iPads.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "By following existing guidelines ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=514"
  },
  {
    "text": "and staying familiar with best practices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's easy to get your app up\nand running for your customers.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-209/?time=518"
  }
]